commentPreTextItems.html: Captain banned for few matches, the Board president resigned, two players doped out of the tournament and where  are Pakistan now? Just 5 runs short of win.

commentTextItems.html: What a great win! Razzaq finishes it off in style. Almost a nonchalant hit. He takes his left foot out of the line, and creams a fullish delivery over long-off. The white ball screams over the boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: What a fabulous win for Pakistan. Younis Khan has run out on to the ground with his players to high-five with the two batsmen. Younis turns around to find Woolmer to his left, goes across and hugs him. He even tries to lift him, Woolmer doesn't seem to mind!  Waqar Younis is out there as well and huge smiles are plastered over all the Pakistani faces. And why not.

Pakistan usually roar when cornered and that's what they did today. To be fair, Sri Lankan spinners were troubled by the dew and were unable to rip it across. But it was their choice to field second. And that as they say is that.
Razzaq at the post-match talk: " I was under pressure, the situation was tense but thanks to god I managed to do the job."

commentTextItems.html: There he goes again. Another whack, wants to finish it off in style,  but can't get under the ball and it rolls towards long-on.

commentTextItems.html: slower ball but Razzaq spots it early, waits for the ball to arrive to cut it past point.
Malik does the sensible thing by pushing one towards long-on. Easy single.
Goes for another big one, a slice over cover but doesn't time it well and it lands in no man's land. I suspect if he had connected well it might have gone down the deep cover's throat
Murderous assault on!  Takes his front foot outside the line again and wallops it straight and clean through the line
bang! sliced over point. Gets his left foot out of the line and slices it over

almost a mix-up. Bill Lawry would have been screaming in joy if he were here. Fullish on the middle and leg, pushed to straightish midwicket, Razzaq, from the non-striker's end, wants a run, Malik doesn't , Jayawardene, who fielded the ball, wishes they ran! but Malik sends Razzaq back in time

stories.seoTitle: Pakistan pull it off as Razzaq treads the razor's edge
stories.summary:
Backed into the corner by the late withdrawal of Shoaib Akhtar and
Mohammad Asif, Pakistan showed incredible self-belief and no little skill
to pull off a splendid four-wicket victory over Sri Lanka in the first
high-quality match of this Champions Trophy
